gomodel:SYNGO_2351  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Beta2 Adrenergic receptor immunoprecipitates together with the L-type calcium channel Cav1.2 (Fig. 1a). Immunolabelling of rat hippocampal sections indicates co-localization with Cav1.2 at synapses using an antibody directed against the Beta2 Adrenergic receptor (Santa Cruz Biotechnology, H-20) (Fig.3).. Experimental description: Fig. legends:\nCrude rat forebrain membranes were extracted ...\nRat hippocampal sections were stained with antibodies..." ;
